By pleading guilty, I am explicitly recognizing the impact of my actions and the harm caused by allowing the company's greenwashing to continue for a brief period of time. I understand that my role in this offense was limited and that the true emission numbers were ultimately exposed by someone else just 5 weeks later, rendering my actions ultimately ineffective. However, I deeply regret my participation in perpetuating the deception and any negative repercussions it may have had.

I want to highlight the significance of this guilty plea as a mitigating factor that benefits the court. By taking ownership of my wrongdoing, I am demonstrating to the court my willingness to be held accountable and cooperate fully with the legal process. This guilty plea not only saves valuable time and resources that would have been spent on a trial but also allows for a more efficient and streamlined legal process.

